// TEST: category callee-blame
// TEST: counterexample-fn "pinned"
// TEST: counterexample-blame callee
// TEST: counterexample-vow-id 1
// TEST: replay confirmed
//
// Counterexample-replay fixture (#335). `pinned`'s `requires: x == 3` forces
// the verifier to pick x=3 for the counterexample, so reconstruction is
// deterministic: the only renderable input is the scalar literal 3. The body
// returns x=3, violating `ensures: result == 0` (vow_id 1, Callee blame).
//
// With `--replay-cex`, both compilers build a `--mode debug` harness that calls
// `pinned(3)` and observe the runtime VowViolation fire with the same vow_id 1
// and Callee blame -> replay "confirmed". No `fn main` here, so the self-hosted
// compiler (which skips replay when the entry file defines main) also confirms.
module ReplayConfirmScalar

fn pinned(x: i64) -> i64 vow {
  requires: x == 3,
  ensures: result == 0
} {
  x
}
